      • readObject

        public Object readObject​(IJsonParsingContext context)
                  throws IOException
        Description copied from interface: IAssemblyClassBinding
        Parses JSON into a bound object.

        This method expects the parser's current token to be:

        • null indicating that the parser has not yet parsed a JSON node, or
        • a JsonToken.START_OBJECT which represents the object containing the data of this assembly.

        After parsing the current token will be the JsonToken.END_OBJECT corresponding to the initial JsonToken.START_OBJECT parsed by this method.

        Specified by:
        readObject in interface IAssemblyClassBinding
        Parameters:
        context - the JSON parser
        Returns:
        the bound object instance representing the JSON object
        Throws:
        IOException - if an error occurred while reading the JSON

        Description copied from interface: INamedModelDefinition
        Indicates if a flag's value can be used as a property name in the containing object in JSON who's value will be the object containing the flag. In such cases, the flag will not appear in the object. This is only allowed if the flag is required, as determined by a true result from IFlagInstance.isRequired(). The IFlagInstance can be retrieved using INamedModelDefinition.getJsonKeyFlagInstance().
        Specified by:
        hasJsonKey in interface INamedModelDefinition
        Returns:
        true if the flag's value can be used as a property name, or false otherwise
        See Also:
        INamedModelDefinition.getJsonKeyFlagInstance()

      • readItem

        public Object readItem​(Object parentInstance,
                       StartElement start,
                       IXmlParsingContext context)
                throws IOException,
                       XMLStreamException
        Description copied from interface: IClassBinding
        Reads a XML element storing the associated data in a Java class instance, returning the resulting instance.

        When called the next XMLEvent of the XMLStreamReader2 is expected to be a XMLStreamConstants.START_ELEMENT that is the XML element associated with the Java class.

        After returning the next XMLEvent of the XMLStreamReader2 is expected to be a the next event after the XMLStreamConstants.END_ELEMENT for the XML XMLStreamConstants.START_ELEMENT element associated with the Java class.

        Specified by:
        readItem in interface IClassBinding
        Parameters:
        parentInstance - the Java instance for the object containing this object
        start - the containing start element
        context - the parsing context
        Returns:
        the instance or null if no data was parsed
        Throws:
        IOException - if an error occurred while reading the parsed content
        XMLStreamException - if an error occurred while parsing the content as XML
